Comment: This species is rather widespread in Middle Asia and has been recorded from 
<collectingCountry id="EDF67654EF4DFFF0FF36FF0DFE9FFED6" box="[237,357,248,269]" name="Kyrgyzstan" pageId="2" pageNumber="451">Kyrgyzstan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="EDF67654EF4DFFF0FEA8FF0DFE21FED5" box="[371,475,248,270]" name="Tajikistan" pageId="2" pageNumber="451">Tajikistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="EDF67654EF4DFFF0FE32FF0DFDA7FED5" box="[489,605,248,270]" name="Uzbekistan" pageId="2" pageNumber="451">Uzbekistan</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="EDF67654EF4DFFF0FDB7FF0DFD10FED5" box="[620,746,248,270]" name="Afghanistan" pageId="2" pageNumber="451">Afghanistan</collectingCountry>
, and 
<collectingCountry id="EDF67654EF4DFFF0FCFCFF0DFC87FED5" box="[807,893,248,270]" name="Pakistan" pageId="2" pageNumber="451">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="F1704B35EF4DFFF0FC54FF0DFBC8FED5" author="SMETANA A" box="[911,1074,248,270]" pageId="2" pageNumber="451" pagination="579 - 624" refId="ref5582" refString="SMETANA A. (2004): Subfamily Paederinae FLEMING, 1821. - In: LOBL I. &amp; A. SMETANA (eds), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Volume 2. Hydrophiloidea - Histeroidea - Staphylinoidea. - Apollo Books, Stenstrup: 579 - 624." type="book chapter" year="2004">SMETANA 2004</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation id="F1704B35EF4DFFF0FF69FEE3FE71FEF0" author="ROUGEMONT G" box="[178,395,277,299]" pageId="2" pageNumber="451" pagination="513 - 520" refId="ref5542" refString="ROUGEMONT G. M. DE (1988): Notes on some palearctic Stilicus species with special reference to Turkey (Col. Staphylinidae, Paederinae). - Revue Suisse de Zoologie 95: 513 - 520." type="journal article" year="1988">ROUGEMONT (1988)</bibRefCitation>
distinguished two subspecies, with 
<emphasis id="A795EAD6EF4DFFF0FCE3FEE3FBC7FEF0" box="[824,1085,277,299]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="451">
<taxonomicName id="52E14D47EF4DFFF0FCE3FEE3FC21FEF0" baseAuthorityName="SOLSKY" baseAuthorityYear="1874" box="[824,987,277,299]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Rugilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="451" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prolongatus">R. prolongatus</taxonomicName>
khalash
</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="F1704B35EF4DFFF0FF69FEC6FE94FE93" author="ROUGEMONT G" box="[178,366,306,328]" pageId="2" pageNumber="451" pagination="513 - 520" refId="ref5542" refString="ROUGEMONT G. M. DE (1988): Notes on some palearctic Stilicus species with special reference to Turkey (Col. Staphylinidae, Paederinae). - Revue Suisse de Zoologie 95: 513 - 520." type="journal article" year="1988">ROUGEMONT 1988</bibRefCitation>
distributed in 
<collectingCountry id="EDF67654EF4DFFF0FDDAFEC7FDA3FE93" box="[513,601,306,328]" name="Pakistan" pageId="2" pageNumber="451">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
, but this hypothesis requires confirmation.
</paragraph>
